 specifications and prescriptions. He brings his blended sound to Untitled Basement this weekend. Details: The performance takes place on November 21 and 22 at the Untitled Basement, 7 Reserve Street, Braamfontein. Tickets cost R180 online and R240 at the door. To purchase tickets visit www.quicket.co.za. For more information call 011 339 1647 Picnics in the Sky: Organisers provide patrons with a picnic basket containing eating utensils and a blanket. Patrons are then given 30 minutes to shop at MarketOnMain. Guests are then taken to the 50th floor of the Carlton Centre for a picnic overlooking Johannesburg. Details: The picnic will take place on November 24 starting at Curiocity Backpackers, 302 Fox Street. Entry costs R300. For more information or to purchase tickets visit www.curiocitybackpackers.com or call 072 880 9583 / 011 592 0515 A Resilient Visionary - Poetic Expressions of David Koloane: Under the curation of Thembinkosi Goniwe, this retrospective exhibition looks to highlight the life and work of late artist David Koloane. Details: The exhibition takes place until December 6 at the Standard Bank Art Gallery, Frederick Street, Marshalltown, Johannesburg. For more information call 011 631 4467 Manipulated Image: Lionel Smit’s fourth solo exhibition with Everard Read is inspired by the digital age and the ability to manipulate images. Using silkscreen and oil layering this body of work presents the artists experimentation with portraiture. Details: The exhibition takes place until December 20 at Everard Read, 6 Jellicoe Avenue, Rosebank, Johannesburg. Fore more information visit www.everard-read.co.za or call 011 788 4805 Cheese and wine festival:  Spend your summer weekend indulging in local cheese, wine, craft beer, and gin. Details: The festival takes place on November 23 at the 012 Central Precinct, 381 Helen Joseph Street, Arcadia. Tickets cost R40 to R100 and can be purchased from www.webtickets.co.za. For more information visit marketatthesheds.co.za